This is Bill Vernon. And Daryl Lane. Today we will continue our discussion of
science fiction author Lee Killow. Perhaps our best-received novel to date is

06:41.340 --> 06:49.280
The Doppelganger Gambit, a futuristic police procedure mystery novel. A good
deal of the book's appeal lies in its skillful depiction of the interaction

06:49.280 --> 06:59.040
between police officers. We asked Killow if she got this from first-hand
experience. I haven't had any practical experience in it. I did have a police

06:59.040 --> 07:05.480
officer come up to me at a science fiction convention once when I'd been reading
a chapter of Doppelganger, and he asked me when I worked in law enforcement.

07:07.240 --> 07:21.780
Once I decided I wanted to write a mystery science fiction, I went ahead and did
more research, and I've kept into it. And of course, that book itself and others

07:21.780 --> 07:34.860
have brought me into contact with more police officers, and they've passed on a
lot of material to me. And so, short of actually working in it myself, I have

07:34.860 --> 07:44.540
gotten very familiar with it. And I suppose I keep reading about it, or writing
about it, because it was interesting, and because I've all done so much research

07:44.540 --> 07:55.000
on it that it's a shame not to use the material. Killow's slang term for a
police person in The Doppelganger Gambit is Leo. We asked her to explain the

07:55.000 --> 08:05.480
origin of this expression. I would think I was seeing something about law
enforcement officers one time, and I noticed that it made Leo, and I thought,

08:05.620 --> 08:18.060
that's great, because it gave rise in my mind to all kinds of connotations, and
I could see police officers enjoying being called Leos because of the lion, the

08:18.060 --> 08:28.960
fierce kind of association you get with it, and therefore calling police
stations lion dens. And someone who's likely to be picked up by the police is

08:28.960 --> 08:39.640
lion meat. The memorable lead characters in The Doppelganger Gambit, both Leos,
are partnered throughout the book. They manage to transcend all sexual and

08:39.640 --> 08:49.660
philosophical barriers ultimately to solve the case. Listen as Killow explains
how she came up with the characters of Jana Brill and Mama Maxwell. Somewhere in

08:49.660 --> 08:59.200
the beginning, when I was putting the book together, which had started as a
novelette, and I knew it couldn't be a novelette because here I was 15 pages

08:59.200 --> 09:07.620
into something and just barely starting it, I had decided I wanted to use a lady
cop. So for contrast,

09:08.560 --> 09:20.840
I gave her a male partner, and I can't remember why I decided to make him black.
It was one of these things that just kind of happened. Somebody later pointed

09:20.840 --> 09:29.500
out that I had my female character was the one that was working by the book and
procedure, and my male character was the one who was working on intuition, which

09:29.500 --> 09:38.500
is an interesting reverse on the way people generally think of males and
females. And that just sort of happened. The characters sort of balanced one

09:38.500 --> 09:48.880
another, but a lot of the balance was unconscious on my part. Jana Brill and
Mama Maxwell are a fascinating pair. We asked Killow if she plans to use them

09:48.880 --> 09:58.520
again. They were fun characters, and I intend to work with them again. Killow
wrote another police procedure novel set in the same future history. This book

09:58.520 --> 10:07.660
is called Deadly Silence, with a T. In this novel, Terran Leos are transported
to the planet Agar to function as peace officers. There, they must operate under

10:07.660 --> 10:17.140
different rules. Their first duty is to aid the victims of crimes, rather than
to pursue the perpetrator. How did Killow come up with this role? I suppose it

10:17.140 --> 10:30.700
reflects a little bit of a reaction to some of the things that I've seen in our
own culture, where the victim suffers a lot because everybody's so interested in

10:30.700 --> 10:38.940
catching the guy who did it that a lot of times they're not paying too much
attention to the victim himself. In another twist, the Leos must function as

10:38.940 --> 10:44.420
defense attorneys when the perpetrator is brought to trial. Tomorrow, more on
author Lee Killow.

